\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 4. L. trichophyllum} Schousboe, {\i Vextr. Marokko} 154 (1800) (incl.{\i  L. grandiflorum} DC.). Bulb 10-20 mm in diameter. Leaves 4-12(-20) cm, narrowly linear, developed before anthesis. Scape 8-30 cm, slender. Umbel of 2-4 flowers; spathe 15-30 mm, 2-valved; pedicels up to 60 mm, the longest usually exceeding the spathe. Perianth-segments 12-20(-25) mm, white, sometimes tinged with pink, the outer 3 apiculate. Style filiform, slightly exceeding the stamens. Seeds without strophiole. Flowering in spring. 2n = 14.{\i  Dry, sandy ground. S.W. & S.C. Spain, S. & C. Portugal. }Hs Lu.
